<ns3327:section xmlns:ns3327="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.security.protectingSourceCode.layoutObfuscation">
    
    <ns3328:title xmlns:ns3328="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Layout Obfuscation</ns3328:title>

<ns3329:para xmlns:ns3329="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Layout obfuscation is the simplest approach to obfuscation which can make
reverse engineering significantly more difficult without incurring a performance
penalty.</ns3329:para>
<ns3330:para xmlns:ns3330="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
Layout obfuscators changes elements of the byte code which will not affect
the execution of the application. It includes
<ns3331:itemizedlist xmlns:ns3331="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <ns3332:listitem xmlns:ns3332="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3333:formalpara xmlns:ns3333="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3334:title xmlns:ns3334="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identifier scrambling</ns3334:title><ns3335:para xmlns:ns3335="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> including renaming of variable, method and 
       class names.</ns3335:para></ns3333:formalpara></ns3332:listitem>
  <ns3336:listitem xmlns:ns3336="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3337:formalpara xmlns:ns3337="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3338:title xmlns:ns3338="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Comment scrambling</ns3338:title><ns3339:para xmlns:ns3339="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">which involves altering the comments in the code.</ns3339:para></ns3337:formalpara></ns3336:listitem>
</ns3331:itemizedlist>
</ns3330:para>
    
</ns3327:section>